   0 & { - \alpha }  \cr 
   \alpha  & 0  \cr 

 } } \right]$$, where $$\alpha$$ is a non-zero real number an $$N = \sum\limits_{k = 1}^{49} {{M^{2k}}} $$. If $$(I - {M^2})N =  - 2I$$, then the positive integral value of $$\alpha$$ is ____________.

